Um 4h ein Herr Tischler;
              Possibly Hans Tischler (1915–2010). A Viennese by birth, he received a Ph.D. from the University of Vienna in 1937 on Mahler, and from Yale University in 1942 on Notre Dame polyphony; in the USA, he had a long and distinguished career as a musicologist, primarily as a medieval music scholar.
